<description>
<![CDATA[<a href="https://instagram.com/p/DCsKC3KR3N8/">View on Instagram</a><p><img src="https://scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/468131046_17883639966174016_7865328447540158878_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=104&_nc_ohc=a8jNwYiPDRUQ7kNvgFvXcuA&_nc_gid=076d5073516c4fac91ff2f733fa1ecba&edm=AGenrX8BAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AYB6BtZ0XOH8ZXNEghwxO616V9dBpSnSr0sej0XyDwa3ig&oe=677E3D54&_nc_sid=ed990e" /><br>Here’s a step by step if you want to do this yourself: Clean out tank with fresh gas then drain, fill to the brim with about 1/2 Distilled Vinegar and 1/2 Tap water, wait for reaction to finish so it no longer smells like vinegar, agitate then flush with hose/pressure washer, rinse well with distilled water, then swish a cup of WD-40 to displace the rest of the water. Dry on a hot driveway. #diy #motorcycles #cleaning #restoration #1978Yamaha #xs1100]]>
</description>
